    {
      "note_no": "93",
      "note": "The term julud (sing, jild) denotes, literally, \"skins\", but apparently comprises here also the wool which grows on the skins of domesticated animals. It is to be noted that in Arabian usage the noun bayt (\"house\") signifies not only a solid building but also a \"tent\" - in brief, every kind of dwelling, whether permanent or temporary."
    },
    {
      "note_no": "94",
      "note": "Wabar (here given in its plural, awbar) is the soft wool growing on the shoulders of camels (\"camel-hair\"), used in the weaving of fine cloths and sometimes also of bedouin tents."
    }
